repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
This is an attempt to address #1407. In particular the case where there is a struct with array members, followed by a single element of the same type, such as:

```cython
ctypedef struct SameTypeAfterArraysStruct:
    double a[16]
    double b[16]
    double c
```

A new test is included for this also.  I _think_ this addresses the issue with no side-effects (based on a before and after comparison of the test suite results).  This is also my first PR to Cython and attempt to look into the code base, so my apologies if I have misused some terminology.

There are also more thorough and low-level buffer format tests in `tests/buffers/buffmt.pyx` that do not require NumPy to run, and thus are preferable for this kind of parsing test.

The tests here are still good as integration tests, though, so keep them.

commit.message: Fix memoryview of structs with array members
Add test case for memoryview of struct with member following array of same type
Fix C condition syntax in Buffer.c
Add another test for more complicated parsing of struct with arrays
Fix to buffer format array parsing
Add buffer format tests for structs with arrays

title: Memoryviews of arrays of structs fix
